by, Wirral, Merseyside, Lancashire, England":"Wirral, Merseyside, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gibson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Older Scots personal name   Gibb   (a pet form of <i>Gilbert</i>) + <i>son</i>, hence ‘son of <i>Gibb</i>’. The name is very common in Ireland, having arrived in that country in the 17th century. It is also occasionally adopted for <i>Ó Gibealláin</i>, see   Giblin  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gibb","meanings":["English: from the personal name <i>Gibb</i>, a pet form of <i>Gilbert</i> (compare   Gibbs  ). This surname is also frequent in Scotland."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Gibson II was born in 1336, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Lord John Gibson, was 36 and his mother, Lora De La Hay De Cummingesburgh, was 36. He married Elizabeth Ramgay about 1357, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died about 1408, in Wirral, Merseyside, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1336–Abt 1408":"1336–umbes 1408","1336–1408":"1336–1408","1349–1389":"1349–1389","1340–1375":"1340–1375","1358–1448":"1358–1448","1362–1467":"1362–1467","1300–1349":"1300–1349","1300–1367":"1300–1367","Abt 1408":"umbes 1408","1362":"1362","1340":"1340","1448":"1448","1349":"1349","1336":"1336","1358":"1358","after 1349":"pärast 1349","1467":"1467","1367":"1367","1389":"1389","1300":"1300","1375":"1375","about 1357":"umbes 1357","1408":"1408","Yorkshire, England":"Y